<section class="entry background-section" id="background" aria-labelledby="background-title">
  <div class="bg-head">
    <div class="section-kicker">A little about me</div>
    <h2 id="background-title">The longer story.</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-body">
    <p class="bg-lede">
      I grew what started as a Wix site into a marketplace doing over
      <strong>$400,000 a year</strong> in sales. A decade of marketing
      behind that — building my own startups and consulting across dozens
      of industries. Now I write about it, and build for a few operators a
      year.
    </p>

    <figure class="bg-photo">
      <img
        src="/assets/david-fsu-donation.jpg"
        alt="A young David Russell, second from left, presenting a donation check to the FSU College of Business, standing with two friends and the dean."
        loading="lazy"
        width="600"
        height="400"
      />
      <figcaption>
        Donating to the FSU College of Business as a student — ten years before
        any of this. <span class="bg-photo-meta">Second from left.</span>
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <p class="bg-prose">
      The work has always been the same shape: figure out what is actually
      useful, ship it cleanly, then keep tightening the loop between offer,
      audience, and the thing they buy. Some of it was mine end-to-end. A
      lot of it was alongside operators who needed a marketing brain that
      could also build the site, write the copy, and run the funnel.
    </p>

    <p class="bg-prose">
      Longer version lives on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/heydavidr/">LinkedIn</a>.
      Tools, books, and people I recommend are on the <a href="/recommended/">recommended page</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* Background section — narrow editorial column, centered. No split,
     no stats cards. The stats already appear in the hero so we don't
     repeat them here — different content, different shape. */
  .background-section {
    text-align: left;
  }
  .bg-head {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto 32px;
  }
  .bg-head h2 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(40px, 5.2vw, 64px);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--star);
    max-width: 16ch;
  }
  .bg-body {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .bg-lede {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2vw, 24px);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--star);
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    letter-spacing: -0.012em;
  }
  .bg-lede strong {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--signal);
  }
  .bg-prose {
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--mist);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }
  .bg-prose a {
    color: var(--star);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(91, 141, 239, 0.35);
  }
  .bg-prose a:hover {
    color: var(--signal);
    border-bottom-color: var(--signal);
  }

  /* Editorial photo with caption — Substack/Medium-style, full column width */
  .bg-photo {
    margin: 36px 0 32px;
  }
  .bg-photo img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    box-shadow: 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04) inset,
                0 18px 50px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45);
  }
  .bg-photo figcaption {
    margin-top: 14px;
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--mist);
    line-height: 1.45;
    text-align: left;
  }
  .bg-photo-meta {
    margin-left: 10px;
    color: var(--smoke);
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-style: normal;
    font-size: 13px;
  }
</style>
